<exercise checkit-seed="0005" checkit-slug="P5" checkit-title="Expected Value">
    <statement>
                <p> Dennis is gambling at a roullette wheel. The wheel has 17 equally sized spots. 6 of the spots are winning locations, and the rest are losing. If costs \$8 to play the wheel. If Dennis wins, they get their bet back and they win \$20, otherwise they forfeit their bet. What is the expected value of this gamble?
                </p>
        
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            The expected value is <m>\frac{6}{17}(20) + \frac{11}{17}(-8) = $1.88</m>
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
